snippet.textDisplay: Have you played The Last Guardian? The soundtrack is immense. Once you play through the game, each song has such deep emotional pulls that bring you right back to that spot in the game. I haven't experienced anything like that from a game in a long time. It's a fantastic game and if you have the chance to go through it you definitely should!

snippet.textDisplay: You know, I don't know if I ever thanked you man. Years ago I had looked for Super Mario Galaxy music (the only game I owned) because I loved the sound so much, and I found your channel. You introduced me to so many cool pieces from games I'd never heard of. Dustforce has an INCREDIBLE soundtrack!!! So thanks again! Now I cover video game music on my harp, and I don't know how I would've fallen in love with it in the first place without channels like yours. Thank you SupraDarky! ❤️

snippet.textDisplay: I really wish Lifeformed had worked on more OSTs since this game's release 5 years ago. It has to be one of my favorite indie game soundtracks. I really like this track's more disjointed structure and sound effects, it makes your ears work in a pleasant way.
